A B O U T  :
===================================
BAST (Back And Synchronization Tools) is a set of tools to minimize
the effort required to create, archive, rotate, synchronize backups.

T R Y   I T   O U T :
===================================
* Get yourself a copy of the code.
* From your command line, cd to the base BAST directory.
* Pick the command that suits your OS:
  Unix/Linux/BSD/OSX: ./bast.sh --conf doc/examples/project1.conf
  Windows: ./bast.bat --conf doc/examples/project1.conf
* You may also try --help for more help.